				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">A couple questions from a rusty bard...<a name="10723"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 19 03 12:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been away from my bard for way too long and had a couple questions for anyone that had/wanted to answer.
<br />

<br />
If I remember correctly, there was a problem with our mezzes overwriting enchanter mezzes.  As I recall if I mezzed after a chanter did, it would overwrite theirs and then we have the shorter duration mezz to worry about.  I thought they were going to fix it so that chanter one would block ours.  Is this still the case?  I've been playing alot this weekend and have been worried about messing up the chanters rythmn so haven't been helping with lock down.  Is it the general consensus that we should mezz first and have them overwrite ours?  If that's the case, how do you all work it?  Do you have a hotkey that says mezzing this one, assist me for target or soemthign to that affect?
<br />

<br />
I'm very poorly equipped but haven't had any problems with it till now and decided to look into upgrading.  I'm hesitant to list gear here since I don't want you all laughing so hard you can't finish reading this post. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  I'm thinking of getting Heraldic made from a very generous friend and was wondering it that's pretty decent armor for my level.  I just replaced lambent legs with the moss covered ones from Veksar, but was looking at all the hp/mana on the heraldic armor.  Friend loaned me his to try out and it gave me alot more hp's/mana which very nice to see, not to mention the AC was a big bonus.  Since I can get this fairly cheap (already have the sunlights and BD needed) is it wise to upgrade to this till something better comes along?  I heard a rumor that there may be a quest allowing us to change dieties in the next expansion (ldon I think) but seems that's an old rumor from the last 3 expansions so don't want to wait around for it if it's not going to happen.
<br />

<br />
And finally...  Can anyone explain how the 56 song that ports them to bind works?  It says on casters realm (I know, usually wrong) that after it gates them back to bind, it'll mem wipe them.  I just got 56 yesterday and wanted to test it out on an outing in Veksar so tried it on first mob pulled after letting group know what I was doing.  It gated like it was supposed to, but then the chanter got summoned.  Is this normal or did I catch it while he was mid cast and his hit after I gated?  What are some handy uses for this if it doesn't mem wipe?  I could think of some cool looking trains I could cause<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> or maybe for vacating a premisis by running away and sending  all the mobs on my tail back to their binds.  Are there any secrets/tricks for using this spell?  Seems too cool to not use.
<br />

<br />
In closing, thanks for your time and I appreciate any input that you could add.  A little about me....  My main is a Shaman(Bodabag) I'd play while my bard was farming for scales for epic.  Now shaman is 65 and bard has no epic scales.  /sigh.  So I gave up trying to get the scales the old fashioned way and am back to playing the bard cuz I always missed him and what he could do.  Bards name is Hooligo and we live on Inny server.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
