				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple questions from a rusty bard...<a name="10745"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 20 03 5:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Bard mez still overwrites chanter mez; I haven't seen anything that proves otherwise.  It also seems to get a bit more complicated:  If a chanter mezzes a mob that a bard already had mez'd, the chanter mez will wear off when the bard's mez would have.  That means if the chanter is going to take over mezzing a mob, he should let your mez wear off first or be ready to remez in 18 seconds or less.  This is why I stay out of the cc unless the chanter dies or there wasn't one to start with.  Make 'em do their job hehe!
<br />

<br />
Fierce Heraldic armor is awesome.  I wish I was Rallos Zek instead of Agnostic so I could wear it.  Many people I know argue that it's too overpowered compared to the other cultural stuff.  Wear it proudly if you can.
<br />

<br />
The song doesn't remove anyone from the hate list.  The mob will come back, and he might bring friends.  Handy uses include finding Eldrig the Old's PH in Skyfire, interrupting casters if (and only if) you're fighting at their spawn point, and in conjunction with Fading Memories to split pull.  You can pull two, gate one, FM, and pull the one you didn't gate, OR pull the whole camp, gate one, FM, and have your group pull the gated mob before the others path back to their camp.
<br />

<br />
I think Solkarr is right about the dots, you must be using a drum that's better than a regular store-bought one.  The exception to &quot;store-bought&quot; is combine hand drums from the vendors in Katta.  I'm pretty sure the combine instruments have a small instrument mod.  Either way, if you buy a drum from the Freeport bard guild it should give you the numbers Reed says it will.
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
~Pele
