				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple questions from a rusty bard...<a name="10795"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 24 03 9:32 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I bought a bunch of Fierce Heraldic armor and absolutely love it.  In my situation, I play a Warrior and a Bard on the same account.  Using the shared bank slots, I can actually change armor back and forth depending on who I want to play that day.  So even though it's expensive, I'm getting twice the bang for the buck on it.  However, I do wish my cha was higher, and that's one thing that donning armor primarily made for a warrior will do for you:  provide no charisma boost.  However, a cloak of greater pernicity (+25 cha), an illusion mask and some +cha rings to swap in for when I'm doing a lot crowd control are my personal solution (as well two +25 cha steins aren't to be scoffed at if you are needing to lock down a number of problematic mobs at once).   The extravagent amounts of HP and AC are life savers many times over.
<br />

<br />
I'm no longer in a raid/uber guild (used to be with another char but don't care for it) so with my small family guild, this is about the best I'm going to do for myself for a very long time.  It was a good choice, so I recommend getting the heraldic if you can, just plan to boost your cha in other ways since you will indeed want that.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
